INSERT INTO `dbmanagement_solution` VALUES (1689,'200404003030','(i) Tabulate all possible products:;img;Tabulate frequency / probability distribution:;img;;$$E(X) = \\sum_{all x_{i}} x_{i}.P(X = x) $$;$$= (1)\\left(\\frac{6}{36}\\right) + (2)\\left(\\frac{12}{36}\\right) + (3)\\left(\\frac{6}{36}\\right) + (4)\\left(\\frac{6}{36}\\right) + (6)\\left(\\frac{6}{36}\\right) $$;$$= 3$$;;$$E(X^{2}) = \\sum_{all x_{i}} {x_{i}}^{2}.P(X = x) $$;$$= (1)^{2}\\left(\\frac{6}{36}\\right) + (2)^{2}\\left(\\frac{12}{36}\\right) + (3)^{2}\\left(\\frac{6}{36}\\right) + (4)^{2}\\left(\\frac{6}{36}\\right) + (6)^{2}\\left(\\frac{6}{36}\\right)$$;$$= \\frac{35}{3}$$;;$$\\therefore Var(X) = E(X^{2}) - [E(X)]^{2}$$;$$ = \\left(\\frac{35}{3}\\right) - (3)^{2} = \\frac{8}{3}$$;;(ii) ;Let n = sample size = 100;Let p = P(X = 2) = $$\\frac{12}{36}$$ = $$\\frac{1}{3}$$ and q = 1 - p = $$\\frac{2}{3}$$;T ~ B(n,p);Since n(= 100) is large and np$$\\left(= \\frac{100}{3}\\right)$$ > 5 and nq$$\\left(= \\frac{200}{3}\\right)$$ > 5;X ~ N(np, npq) = N $$\\left(\\frac{100}{3}, \\frac{200}{9}\\right)$$ approximately ;P(T $$\\geq$$ 40);$$\\equiv$$ P(T > 39.5) $$\\leftarrow$$ continuity correction;$$\\equiv$$ P$$\\left(Z > \\frac{39.5 - np}{\\sqrt{npq}}\\right)$$ = P $$\\left(Z > \\frac{39.5-\\frac{100}{3}}{\\sqrt{\\frac{200}{9}}} \\right)$$;= P(Z > 1.3081) = 1 - $$\\Phi$$(1.308);= 1 - 0.9045 = 0.0955(3sf)'),(1690,'200404003031','(i) ;Let n = sample size = 50;Let $$\\mu_{0}$$ = assume $$\\mu$$ = 9.5;Let $$\\sigma^{2}$$ = Var(X) = 15;;$$\\hat{\\mu} = \\overline{x} = \\frac{\\sum x}{n} = \\frac{527.1}{50} = 10.542$$;Test $$H_{0}: \\mu = \\mu_{0}$$ against $$H_{1}: \\mu \\neq \\mu_{0}$$ a 2-tailed test for difference;At 5% significance level, critical value $$z_{0.025}$$ = 1.960;Reject $$H_{0}$$ if $$\\left| z \\right| > \\left| z_{0.025} \\right|$$;Under $$H_{0}$$, the test statistic is ;$$z = \\left( \\frac{\\overline{x} - \\mu_{0}}{\\sigma / \\sqrt{n}} \\right) = \\frac{10.542 - 9.5}{\\sqrt{15/50}} = 1.902$$;;Since $$\\left| z \\right| < \\left| z_{0.025} \\right|$$, do not reject $$H_{0}$$ and conclude that, at the 5% significance level, there is insufficient evidence that $$\\mu \\neq 9.5$$;;(ii);Let $$\\mu_{1}$$ = alternative assume $$\\mu = 11.5$$;With $$\\hat{\\mu}(= 10.542) < \\mu_{1}(= 11.5)$$, in a 1-tailed test with $$H_{0}: \\mu < \\mu_{1}$$;$$\\hat{\\sigma}^{2} = \\frac{1}{n-1}\\left[\\sum x^{2} - \\frac{1}{n}\\left(\\sum x\\right)^{2}\\right]$$;= $$\\frac{1}{49}\\left[6172.31 - \\frac{1}{50}\\left(527.1\\right)^{2}\\right]$$ = 12.56;For a 1-tailed test, the $$\\alpha$$% critical value is $$z_{\\alpha}$$;Under $$H_{0}$$, the test statistic is ;$$z = \\left( \\frac{\\overline{x} - \\mu_{1}}{\\sigma / \\sqrt{n}} \\right) = \\frac{10.542 - 11.5}{\\sqrt{12.56/50}} = -1.911$$;$$H_{0}$$ is accepted if $$z > - z_{\\alpha}$$;;i.e. -1.911 > -$$z_{\\alpha}$$;$$z_{\\alpha}$$ > 1.911;$$\\equiv \\Phi(z_{\\alpha}) > \\Phi(1.911)$$ ;$$\\equiv 1 - \\alpha > 0.9720$$;$$\\therefore \\alpha < 0.028$$;$$\\equiv$$ Significance level of test < 2.8%'),(1691,'200503003001','$$\\theta = 30^{\\circ}$$ is a root of $$2 - \\cos ^{2}\\theta = \\lambda \\cos 2\\theta$$;$$\\Rightarrow 2 - \\cos^{2}30^{\\circ} = \\lambda \\cos 2(30^{\\circ})$$;$$2 - \\left(\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}\\right)^{2}  = \\frac{1}{2} \\lambda$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\lambda = \\frac{5}{2}$$;$$\\therefore$$ Equation is:;$$2 - \\cos^{2}\\theta = \\frac{5}{2} \\cos 2 \\theta $$;$$4 - 2 \\cos^{2}\\theta = \\frac{5}{2} ( 2 \\cos^{2} \\theta - 1)$$;$$2 \\ cos^{2} \\theta = 9$$;$$\\cos^{2}\\theta = \\frac{3}{4}$$;$$\\cos\\theta = \\pm \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}$$;$$\\theta = 360 n^{\\circ} \\pm 30^{\\circ}$$ or $$360 n^{\\circ} \\pm 150^{\\circ}$$;For $$0^{\\circ} \\leq \\theta \\leq 360^{\\circ}$$, besides $$\\theta = 30^{\\circ}, \\theta= 150^{\\circ} ,210^{\\circ}$$ or $$330^{\\circ}$$'),(1692,'200503003002','$$1 + \\left | 2x -3  \\right | = 3x \\Rightarrow \\left | 2x -3  \\right | = 3x -1$$;;For $$2x - 3 > 0 \\Rightarrow x > 